leetcode:- 237. Delete Node in a Linked List

ques:- ðŸ“Œ Problem Summary

You are given only access to the node that needs to be deleted in a singly linked list (not the head).
You must delete that node from the list.

âš ï¸ Important Constraint

You cannot access the head of the list.
You cannot traverse backwards.
The node to delete is not the tail.

approach:-

class Solution {
public:
    void deleteNode(ListNode* node) {
        node->val=node->next->val;
        node->next=node->next->next;
    }
};